From: Dan <dvonlineservices123@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 06:17:50 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add ErrorBoundary around report, articles, timeline,
 hero, and app

Wraps each major render subtree in a reusable class-based ErrorBoundary
so a bad data shape from /api/report or /api/articles degrades one
section instead of blanking the whole page.

- New src/components/ErrorBoundary.jsx: catches render errors, shows a
  styled fallback (or silent null when fallback={null}), and resets
  itself when resetKey changes so users recover by switching dates.
- App.jsx wraps BroadcastHero (silent fallback), TimelineView,
  ArticlesView, the analysis report, and the entire App tree with a
  top-level boundary that catches anything above the per-section ones.
- Defensive sourceCount() guards against story.articles being null or
  undefined, which is the same class of bug the boundaries catch at
  render time but worth handling inline since this runs in App.jsx's
  body above the analysis boundary.
